external_knowledge:
- 'shipped' status indicates that the order has been dispatched to the customer;
- 'total_stock > 0' ensures that the product has available stock;
- 'size_s' specifically refers to the 'Small' size of the product.

- 'Top' products refer to clothing items such as t-shirts, blouses, and sweaters;
- Lead time is the duration it takes for a supplier to deliver a product after an order is placed;
- Recent orders are those placed within the last 30 days.

- "blossomed" refers to products that have experienced a positive inventory change;
- "gardeners" refers to suppliers who have contributed to the positive inventory change;
- "last month" is defined as the period from one month ago to the current date.

- "blossoms of products" refers to the products in the database;
- "nurturing suppliers" refers to the supplier companies that provide the products;
- "harvest of sales exceeding a dozen" means the total quantity sold is greater than 10.

- The "sold products" refer to items that have been ordered and are associated with an order ID in the `orders` table;
- The "full size availability" includes all possible sizes from XXS to 4XL for each product;
- The "customer's first name, last name, and email" are used to identify the customer who made the purchase.

- "grown to a medium size" refers to products that have size M available in stock;
- "ordered more than 10 times" refers to the total quantity of orders for the product in size M being greater than 10;
- "meet their supplier's minimum order quantity" means the quantity ordered for each product is at least equal to the supplier's minimum order quantity.

- "Top three best-selling products" refers to the products with the highest total sales amount;
- "Size category" is determined by the size of the product;
- "Stars in a constellation of sales" is a metaphorical expression to describe the top-ranking products.

- "Most recent orders" refers to orders placed with the latest dates;
- "Product movements" include both sales and restocks, as indicated by the inventory change reasons;
- "Stock levels" are inferred from the latest change amounts, which can be positive (restock) or negative (sale).

- "Top three" refers to the products with the highest total revenue;
- "Revenue" is calculated as the sum of the quantity ordered multiplied by the unit price and adjusted for any discounts applied;
- The time period considered is the year 2023.
